
Global Configuration:
Standardisation - Min-Max
Maximum number of iterations: 500000

CommandLine Arguments:
--alpha: learning rate
--lambda: regularization factor
--p-norm: p-norm to use (4, 6 etc)
--basis: basis function to use (options: sigmoid or normal)
--train: path to training dataset file (relative or absolute)
--test: path to test dataset file (relative or absolute)
===============================================================================================
Question 1:
mean squared error on the test samples using all the features with L2 norm

learning_rate = 0.0001
lambda_regularizer = 5000
Run using command:
python lr.py --alpha 0.0001 --lambda 5000 --train train.csv --test test.csv


Report the mean squared error on the test samples when the predictor is unregularized

learning_rate = 0.01
lambda_regularizer = 0
Run using command:
python lr.py --lambda 0 --alpha 0.01 --train train.csv --test test.csv

===============================================================================================

Question 3:
Modify your implementation to allow for a p-norm regularizer where p can take any one of the
three values [2, 4, 6].
Report mean squared errors on the test samples when p = 4 and p = 6.

norm p = 4
learning_rate = 0.0001
lambda_regularizer = 80000
Run using command:
python lr.py --alpha 0.0001 --lambda 80000 --p-norm 4 --train train.csv --test test.csv

norm p = 6
learning_rate = 0.0001
lambda_regularizer = 80000
Run using command:
python lr.py --alpha 0.0001 --lambda 80000 --p-norm 6 --train train.csv --test test.csv

===============================================================================================

Question 4:
Implement two different basis functions that will be applied to your input features with the L2-
regularized model.

basis function 1:
learning_rate = 0.0003
lambda_regularizer = 750
Run using command:
python lr.py --alpha 0.0003 --lambda 750 --basis sigmoid --train train.csv --test test.csv

basis function 2:
learning_rate = 0.0001
lambda_regularizer = 8500
Run using command:
python lr.py --basis normal --alpha 0.0001 --lambda 8500 --train train.csv --test test.csv

================================================================================================

Question 5:
For this part, you have free reign. You can implement any enhancements to the regularized linear
regression model that you think your model could benefit from. Please describe your innovations
within the file.

learning_rate = 0.001
lambda_regularizer = 105000
p-norm 6
Run using command:
python lr.py --lambda 105000 --alpha 0.001 --basis sigmoid --p-norm 6 --train train.csv --test test.csv
